## API Routes

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | `/students` | Fetch all students |
| POST | `/students` | Add a new student |
| GET | `/halls` | Fetch all halls with occupancy |
| POST | `/halls` | Add a new hall |
| GET | `/courses` | Fetch all courses |
| GET | `/exams` | Fetch all scheduled exams |
| GET | `/enrollments` | Fetch all student-course enrollments |
| POST | `/enroll` | Enroll a student into a course |
| POST | `/allocate` | Trigger the stored procedure |
| GET | `/allocations` | Fetch the full seating plan |
| GET | `/analytics/piechart` | Students per hall (for chart) |
| GET | `/analytics/occupancy` | Hall capacity vs usage |

---

## Frontend Features

- **Student Registry** — add students and view all registered students live
- **Hall Management** — add exam halls with capacity, view occupancy percentage
- **Enroll in Exam** — assign a student to a course so they appear in the allocation
- **Seat Allocation Engine** — select an exam, click Run, watch the stored procedure execute and seats get assigned in real time
- **Live Allocation Log** — shows each assignment as it comes back from the database
- **Full Seating Plan Table** — complete hall-wise, seat-wise breakdown of every student
- **Hall Distribution Chart** — doughnut chart showing how students are spread across halls, updates after every allocation

---

## How to Run Locally

**Prerequisites:** MySQL 8.0+, Node.js 18+

```bash
# 1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/xan-antx/DBMS-Exam-Allocation-System.git
cd DBMS-Exam-Allocation-System

# 2. Import the database schema
mysql -u root -p < schema.sql

# 3. Set your MySQL password in db.js
# Open db.js and update the password field

# 4. Install dependencies
npm install

# 5. Start the server
node server.js

# 6. Open index.html in your browser
```

The server runs at `http://localhost:3000`. The frontend communicates with it via REST API calls.

---

## Sample Data Included

The schema comes preloaded with:
- 6 students across CSE, ECE, EE, ME branches
- 3 courses: DBMS, Data Structures, Networks
- 3 halls: Hall A (cap: 20), Hall B (cap: 20), Hall C (cap: 15)
- 3 scheduled exams
- Students already enrolled in courses

You can run an allocation immediately after setup without adding any data manually.

